The paper discusses a memory-centric system for deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed system also involves hardware architecture and inter-device communication, which could be categorized under computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed system on deep learning applications, which could be classified under computer vision (cs.CV).
